      • unregisterAll

        public final <L extends Listener> void unregisterAll(java.lang.Class<L> type)
        Description copied from interface: ResourceManager
        Unregisters all resources assignable to the specified listener type. A resource is assignable to a given listener type if the listener type supported by the resource is assignable to the given listener type. Resource unregistration hooks are properly invoked for all matched resources during the unregistration process.

        Note that this method collects all exceptions thrown by resources during the unregistration process and propagates them as suppressed exceptions of a ResourceUnregistrationException instance.

        Specified by:
        unregisterAll in interface ResourceManager
        Parameters:
        type - the listener type to which the assignable resources are going be unregistered, not null
